## String Functions ##
ðŸ”¤ Basic String Functions
Function	Description	Example
len()	Returns the length of a string	len("hello") â†’ 5
str()	Converts an object to a string	str(123) â†’ "123"


ðŸ§ª String Checking Methods
Function	Description	Example
isalnum()	True if all characters are alphanumeric	"abc123".isalnum() â†’ True
isalpha()	True if all characters are alphabetic	"abc".isalpha() â†’ True
isdigit()	True if all characters are digits	"123".isdigit() â†’ True
islower()	True if all characters are lowercase	"abc".islower() â†’ True
isupper()	True if all characters are uppercase	"ABC".isupper() â†’ True
isspace()	True if all characters are whitespace	" \t".isspace() â†’ True
startswith()	True if string starts with specified value	"hello".startswith("he") â†’ True
endswith()	True if string ends with specified value	"hello".endswith("lo") â†’ True


ðŸ”„ String Modification Functions
Function	Description	Example
lower()	Converts string to lowercase	"HELLO".lower() â†’ "hello"
upper()	Converts string to uppercase	"hello".upper() â†’ "HELLO"
capitalize()	Capitalizes first character	"hello".capitalize() â†’ "Hello"
title()	Capitalizes first letter of each word	"hello world".title() â†’ "Hello World"
strip()	Removes leading/trailing whitespace	" hello ".strip() â†’ "hello"
lstrip() / rstrip()	Removes leading / trailing whitespace	" hello ".lstrip() â†’ "hello "
replace(old, new)	Replaces substring with new string	"hello".replace("l", "x") â†’ "hexxo"


ðŸ”Ž Searching & Finding
Function	Description	Example
find()	Returns index of first occurrence or -1	"hello".find("e") â†’ 1
rfind()	Returns last index of occurrence	"hello".rfind("l") â†’ 3
index()	Like find() but raises error if not found	"hello".index("e") â†’ 1
count()	Counts occurrences of a substring	"banana".count("a") â†’ 3


ðŸ”— Splitting & Joining
Function	Description	Example
split()	Splits string into list	"a,b,c".split(",") â†’ ['a', 'b', 'c']
rsplit()	Splits from the right	"a,b,c".rsplit(",", 1) â†’ ['a,b', 'c']
join()	Joins elements of a list into a string	",".join(['a','b']) â†’ "a,b"


ðŸ§¬ String Formatting
Function	Description	Example
format()	Formats strings with placeholders	"Hello, {}".format("World") â†’ "Hello, World"
f""	f-strings for formatting (Python 3.6+)	name = "Sam"; f"Hi {name}" â†’ "Hi Sam"